fields.title: Fruity Yogurt Healthy
fields.content: Froyo is advertised to be a healthy alternative to ice cream. Bubble tea is highly sweetened.

fields.title: Fruity Yogurt Dessert
fields.content: A good place for dessert, enough to satisfy any sweet tooth.

fields.title: Fruity Yogurt Frugal
fields.content: Froyo is priced by the ounce, including any fresh toppings you choose to sprinkle on top. Bubble tea has good value. Credit cards only accepted for charges over $5.

fields.title: Fruity Yogurt Fresh
fields.content: Fresh fruits offered as selections for toppings on froyo. Bubble tea is not made fresh.

fields.title: Fruity Yogurt Main
fields.content: A bright and friendly atmosphere with a unique selection of desserts including froyo and bubble tea. Known for their taro flavor. Good for meetings and hangouts.

fields.title: George's Roasters and Ribs Main
fields.content: George's is just down the block from Hoagie Haven and very similar. Owned by the same people, they also sell subs and other late-night delights.

fields.title: Halo Pub Dessert
fields.content: A wide selection of good ice cream flavors to satisfy any craving.

fields.title: Halo Pub Main
fields.content: Fresh made ice cream! This place is fantastic for its quantities and the vast array of flavors. The lines can get a little long, but worth the wait.

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Late-Night
fields.content: After you've had your drinks at Ivy or at an eating club, be sure to stop by the Haven. Order off the black menu! If you order something that appears to be too healthy, you might get a weird look from the employees.

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Coffee
fields.content: Hoagie Haven has an enormous selection of sodas, energy drinks, and canned teas / coffee. At least one of these is sure to perk you up.

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Spicy
fields.content: Get extra hot sauce, jalapenos peppers, and banana peppers on ALL the hoagies you get. Also, if you're getting the Dirty Sanchez, get the extra dirty sanchez

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Vegetarian
fields.content: The omelets are great alternatives to the meat-heavy dishes for vegetarians.

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Frugal
fields.content: Everything at Hoagie Haven is fairly inexpensive. You can get a half version of any sandwich for less than $5. The big sandwiches can be up to $10, but you can easily split them with a friend.

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Fresh
fields.content: There's almost nothing here that's fresh. The only think you get is delicious hoagies

fields.title: Hoagie Haven Main
fields.content: Hoagie Haven is very popular among the Princeton students. It's a late-night hangout for people after having a few drinks. It can be a little chaotic inside. Be sure to stand to the right to place your order.

fields.title: Mehek Spicy
fields.content: Dishes can be made to different levels of spiciness. Spices used vary but generally complement the dishes.

fields.title: Mehek Vegetarian
fields.content: A variety of vegetarian dishes available, with a diverse selection and authentic taste. Try getting the #Sagwala.

fields.title: Mehek Frugal
fields.content: Dishes are small and slightly expensive, but food is authentic and of good quality.

fields.title: Mehek Main
fields.content: A pricier but authentic Indian restaurant. A nice, warm atmosphere inside, with friendly staff. Provides take-out and catering with online or phone reservation. The #naan is fresh and amazing.

fields.title: Naked Pizza Main
fields.content: A chain pizza place that uses fresh / organic ingredients in their pizza. The higher quality ingredients certainly have a positive impact on the tastiness of the pizza.

fields.title: Olives Main
fields.content: Located right on Witherspoon St., Olives has a great lunch selection. They have dozens of different fresh salads as well as a row of fresh made food. Their #chickencurry is one of their more popular dishes.

fields.title: Osteria Procaccini Main
fields.content: A great pizza place located right off of Route 27 (Nassau St.). It's a great place to sit down and have freshly made pizza. The crusts are usually thin, but the red sauce is amazing

fields.title: Panera Bread Main
fields.content: A chain lunch / sandwich shop. The location is very similar to other Panera's.

fields.title: Pjs Pancake House Main
fields.content: A very popular restaurant for Princeton tourists. One of the only places near Princeton that actually serves a brunch. The pancakes are typically overpriced and greasy though.

fields.title: Qdoba Spicy
fields.content: Entrees come with a variety of choices for spicy salsa, with different levels of spiciness. Tobasco and cholula hot sauce are both provided on the side.

fields.title: Qdoba Frugal
fields.content: A good amount of food for the price. Guacamole always costs extra. Rewards system gives a free meal for every 10 entrees.

fields.title: Qdoba Fresh
fields.content: Ingredients are generally fresh or freshly made.

fields.title: Qdoba Main
fields.content: A chain Mexican food place. Not all that different from other Qdoba's. They have a nice selection of food and are pretty good about getting your order done quickly.

fields.title: Small World Coffee Main
fields.content: Popular local coffee shop in Princeton. Located right on Nassau street, it's a great place to grab a cup of coffee.

fields.title: Starbucks Main
fields.content: One of the fancier starbucks right across the street from Princeton University. They have a clover-leaf machine to get fresh ground coffee.

fields.title: Subway Main
fields.content: A chain sandwich shop. The shop is a little cramped, but the value is fantastic.

fields.title: Thai Village Spicy
fields.content: Dishes can range from mild to spicy, though spice is often added arbitrarily, without complementing the taste.

fields.title: Thai Village Dessert
fields.content: Provides a small selection of desserts, including mango sticky rice.

fields.title: Thai Village Frugal
fields.content: Lunch special is priced well and comes with a soup, salad, or spring roll.

fields.title: Thai Village Main
fields.content: A lone Thai place, run by Chinese owners, with good but unauthentic food. A good environment for group or family meals.

fields.title: The Bent Spoon Main
fields.content: Offers authentic, alternative ice-creams. They freshly make ice creams that range in flavor from chocolate to blood-orange. While defeinitely the highest quality ice cream in Princeton, the portions are small and the price is high.

fields.title: Thomas Sweet Frugal
fields.content: It's not the cheapest place for people who want dessert. The smaller cups are usually around $4 and don't have a lot of food. It's best to get a larger cup for around $6 and share if you're trying to save

fields.title: Thomas Sweet Main
fields.content: A popular student hangout ice-cream shop located near the campus of Princeton University. Thomas Sweet's is a classic Princeton establishment, having served the likes of Albert Einstein. They have a variety of ingredients to mix into your ice cream delight from heath bar to graham crackers.

fields.title: Tiger Noodles Frugal
fields.content: Lunch special is well-priced, with a suitable amount of food.

fields.title: Tiger Noodles Main
fields.content: A generic chinese restaurant, run-of-the-mill in everything from taste to price.

fields.title: Tomo Sushi Frugal
fields.content: Lunch special is very well priced and comes with soup and salad.

fields.title: Tomo Sushi Fresh
fields.content: Sushi is made with fresh ingredients, and seafood is of decent quality.

fields.title: Tomo Sushi Main
fields.content: Very small restaurant run by Chinese owners, serving sushi and other Japanese dishes. Very generic and unauthentic, but quick and decently priced.

fields.title: Tortuga's Main
fields.content: A great Mexican place that's located a little bit off the beaten path.

fields.title: Triumph Main
fields.content: The best pub-food in Princeton, and it's actually great quality. They have a wide selection of home-brewed beers and a changing menu that always has a nice selection of delicious food.

fields.title: Wawa Late-Night
fields.content: Wawa is the only place open 24 hours. Be sure to stop by on the way back from the parites!

fields.title: Wawa Coffee
fields.content: Their coffee is surprisingly good. And, they have sizes up to 24oz. Their regular blend is light and balanced: a perfect morning cup of Joe. The Columbian roast is good if you want a little more strength. The coffee is freshest in the morning

fields.title: Wawa Healthy
fields.content: Most of the stuff here is not that healthy for you. The salads are deceiving since they tend to be fairly unhealthy. The best you can do is get something like a cobb salad and use a fat-free dressing.

fields.title: Wawa Dessert
fields.content: A small selection of smoothies, desserts, and baked goods. Generally overly sweetened and generic.

fields.title: Wawa Fast
fields.content: If you come at the right time, you can be in and out right away. But, if you come during lunch or even late-night, you're not going to get served very quickly. Even though they have 4 payment counters, only 2 are typically in use.

fields.title: Wawa Frugal
fields.content: A great place to pick up a cheap bite to eat. Their fulll hoagies are enormous, and they're not that expensive: only $6 or so. You can also load them up with as many toppings as you like

fields.title: Wawa Fresh
fields.content: A small selection of fresh fruits. Sandwiches are typically made with fresh ingredients.

fields.title: Wawa Main
fields.content: Very conveniently located convenience shop right next to the Princeton campus. The only Princeton establishment open 24 hours. Tends to get packed during the wee hours of the morning after the weekend parties.

fields.title: Mediterra Frugal
fields.content: While the high quality food really makes the value of your dollar big here, you're not going to be able to walk out without spending less than $30 / person.

fields.title: Mediterra Main
fields.content: Excellently prepared food right in the heart of Princeton. The environment of Mediterra really captures the feel fo being in the Mediterranean. They have an amazing wine, alcohol, and beer selection, too.

fields.title: Witherspoon Grill Main
fields.content: A wide selection of fresh seafood and meats, including aged steaks. The service is fantastic, and it's right down the block from Princeton University.

fields.title: Princeton Sport's Bar Main
fields.content: A great place to watch a game, grab some bar food, or just have some beers with friends. They have a wide variety of beers sure to please anyone's tastes.

fields.title: Blue Point Grill Main
fields.content: A stunning selection of seafood. It's as if they were located on a beach! What's also great is that you can buy their food for lunch right next door and eat it in the restaurant.

fields.title: Teresa's Cafe Main
fields.content: From the owner: â€œSimple Italian inspired fare in a neighborhood trattoria style atmosphere in Princeton's Palmer Sq. Fresh, local ingredients, seasonal pasta dishes, pizzette and a mostly regional Italian wine list.â€ù

fields.title: Eno Terra Main
fields.content: From the owner: â€œEno Terra - for lovers of good food & exceptional wine. Off D&R Canal in historic Kingston, NJ. Read the NYT review - on our website
